<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1119992-is-this-his-biography-in-this-article">Is this his biography? In this article (https://www.ramdass.org/first-shift-truth/), he states &quot;This may be redundant to some of you that have read my biography...&quot; but I can&#39;t tell if he means a singular book or online articles/wiki/etc? He has a bunch of books so I assume one of them must be a bio??</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1119992'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F29254.Be_Here_Now">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1119992-is-this-his-biography-in-this-article">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1119992-is-this-his-biography-in-this-article">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/73082568-umar-beretta"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1565048089i/73082568._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/73082568-umar-beretta">Umar Beretta</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
It is partly biographical, but the purpose of making references to his own life experience is to share his knowledge. Very much worth reading.
</span>
</div>
